        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 5:56PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 556 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Burkeville, or near Crewe, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small trees and blow around
unsecured objects. Wind impacting handling of high profile
vehicles.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Crewe and Nottoway around 600 PM EDT.
Blackstone around 605 PM EDT.
Spainville around 610 PM EDT.
Wilsons around 615 PM EDT.
Mannboro around 620 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include North Wellville, Irby,
Earls, Ammon, Murdocks, Twin Lakes State Park, Nutbush, Darvills, The
Falls, and Wellville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
